               <p>JOSEPH SHARPE. I am a <rs id="t18270913-329-viclabel1834" type="occupation">gentleman's servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-329-victim2439 t18270913-329-viclabel1834"></join>. On the 22d of August, about half-past eight o'clock in the evening, I was in <placeName id="t18270913-329-crimeloc1835">Smithfield</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-329-crimeloc1835" type="placeName" value="Smithfield"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-329-crimeloc1835" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-329-off1832 t18270913-329-crimeloc1835"></join> - I felt a hand in my right-hand pocket - I turned and caught the prisoner close to me with his hand in my left-hand pocket. I lost my handkerchief from my right hand pocket, and have never seen it since - I had used it not a minute before. I charged him with it, but there was one on each side of me - the other got away.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-329-person2440">
